	(text "SCLK, MOSI and CS resitors place close to MCU,\nother resistors place close to ADC!"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 497.332 198.374 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "a6290d14-125d-4259-9162-ebe35737ee54")
	)
	(text_box "About:\n- ADC circuit for battery voltage and current reading\n- Cell FETs for cell balancing\n\nDesign Parameters:\n- 7-cell battery voltage monitoring (between 2.5V and 4.3V)\n- 7-cell battery balancing (up to 86mA per cell)\n- Current monitoring (up to 20A)\n\nHow to use it:\n1) Battery cells are disabled from ADC by default to disable current leaking from battery when BMS is off. To enable battery reading, set MEAS_CELL to 1\n2) Read differential AINxP - AINxN voltage and multiply with 71.3/3.3 = 21.606 to get batter cell voltage in V\n3) Read battery current by reading voltage between AIN0P and AIN0N. Divide voltage by 0.001 (shunt resisot is 1m ohm) to get current in A\n4) There is a special case to read overall battery voltage by setting MEAS_BATT to 1 (while keeping MEAS_CELL at 1) and read voltage between AIN7P and AIN7N (like you would read cell 7) and multiply result with 74.6/6.6 = 11.303\n5) Balancing circuit for each sell can be enabled individually by setting CELL_x_BAL to 1. While balancer (cell FET) is on, don't read battery voltage, as you could get less precise cell voltage\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 20.32 20.32 0)
		(size 163.83 38.1)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0.3048)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "87a16a1a-d8a1-4991-9cc2-6f11e21e2340")
	)
